Down the creaky stairs he came, in his arms the dusty box from the almost empty attic. 

"Look what I found," he called&nbsp;cheerfully from behind the package. 

He stood there with the box that I&nbsp;kept hidden&nbsp;behind the broken piano and heavy rolls of wallpaper. He stood there looking at me with that stupid, unknowing&nbsp;grin on his face. 



I don't know why I didn't burn that box and everything in it the moment I got it.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;

I finally made time to download Radiohead's newest album called "In Rainbows". The great thing is that they let you choose how much to pay for the mp3 download. Take that, corporate&nbsp;universe!&nbsp; 

So... being the poor leetle lass that I am I paid zilch. But I promise promise promise to get the discbox set as soon as get my monies from work. Which will be a great self-birthday present since they're sending them out starting&nbsp;the first week of December.&nbsp;

---

It isn't Christmas here yet, we still have Holloween. I feel bad that I missed out on the whole trick-or-treat mess except for like those two times I remember, once wearing&nbsp;the yellow Belle gown my grandma made and the other wearing a white sheet, pretending to be a ghost. LOL. 

I am so going to buy a pumpkin. 

Oktoberfest nga pala. *ahem*&nbsp;&nbsp;

---

I registered online for&nbsp;Heroes Evolution (formerly Heroes 360). And again all I can say is Tim Kring is still a frikin gee-knee-us. It's so complicated and crazy and&nbsp;.001% to almost&nbsp;real.&nbsp;ROFL. I can't imagine how they make all this stuff up as they go along and how they're able to&nbsp;spread&nbsp;this psychotic world to... everywhere. EVERYWHERE.

Wooooh.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;

I got my Los Angeles Public Library card today! 

Ang astig ng public library system nila, nakakabaliw. So this is where Californians get their taxes put into: extremely organized and well-stocked shelves, flat screen lcds,&nbsp;a good website, friendly librarians (since college, i've had a fear of menopausal library ladies) dvds and audiobooks.&nbsp; 

Okay, so when it comes to books I can be pretty much a geek. I loooove libraries. I remember when I was around five or&nbsp;six and I always was at the public library in the valley with my mom and sister. I frikin loved books before I even learned to read. My mom told me I used&nbsp;to look through books when I was around three as if I understood what those squiggly black lines meant.&nbsp;

I'm kinda wondering now why I didn't take up a BA in Creative Writing.

Anyway, a few meters away from the West LA Public Library is a store called Cinefile. And Oh. My. Gah. Ohmygah. Para siyang Video 48 (is it 48 or do i forget what the number really is?) pero i-multiply mo yung Video 48 by 100. 

So parang, 
&nbsp; 
VideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideoVideo 4800. 

Pero di pa ako pwedeng bumili o humiram. Kasi wala pa akong pera. Hihintayin ko pa ang first paycheck. Balak ko every paycheck, bibili ako ng isang dvd. Yahoo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;

Today is Columbus Day. Which means no work for Aliah and shopping for&nbsp;us tres marias. Nakakaiyak magshopping kung puro sale dahil sa mga ewang holiday (yeah columbus, we talked about you in geology class and you're not as great as you think you are).&nbsp;

At! Sa Ross, may nakita akong familiar na dress. Isa siyang dress na&nbsp;puti na may black na ribbons. Isa siyang dress na kapareho ng pinili namin&nbsp;para sa isang babae para sa graduation nung&nbsp;April.&nbsp;Anyway, it cost&nbsp;$56,&nbsp;and if my memory is still serving me correctly, that's much more than the dress we saw in the Philippines. Hehe.&nbsp;Baka Made in the Philippines.&nbsp;

Ahay.

Fast forward.

A full day of Macy's incredibdibdibdible&nbsp;prices and Mrs. Field's cookies and we drive&nbsp;home. No sooner do we get home does my sister go off on a&nbsp;*surprise!!* date. Aba.&nbsp;Nuff said.

I'm starting work on Friday.

Man, I wonder if we still have pizza in the fridge..
&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;
